{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":550,"text":"For the past few years,"},{"time":2040,"text":"I've been spending my summers\nin the marine biological laboratory"},{"time":6393,"text":"in Woods Hole, Massachusetts."},{"time":8931,"text":"And there, what I've been doing\nis essentially renting a boat."},{"time":13117,"text":"What I would like to do is ask you"},{"time":15741,"text":"to come on a boat ride with me tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19836,"text":"So, we ride off from Eel Pond\ninto Vineyard Sound,"},{"time":24753,"text":"right off the coast of Martha's Vineyard,"},{"time":27288,"text":"equipped with a drone\nto identify potential spots"},{"time":30649,"text":"from which to peer into the Atlantic."},{"time":33150,"text":"Earlier, I was going to say\ninto the depths of the Atlantic,"},{"time":36453,"text":"but we don't have to go too deep\nto reach the unknown."},{"time":40311,"text":"Here, barely two miles away"},{"time":42906,"text":"from what is arguably the greatest\nmarine biology lab in the world,"},{"time":47476,"text":"we lower a simple\nplankton net into the water"},{"time":50721,"text":"and bring up to the surface"},{"time":52566,"text":"things that humanity rarely\npays any attention to,"},{"time":55990,"text":"and oftentimes has never seen before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59260,"text":"Here's one of the organisms\nthat we caught in our net."},{"time":62228,"text":"This is a jellyfish."},{"time":63881,"text":"But look closely,"},{"time":65217,"text":"and living inside of this animal\nis another organism"},{"time":68232,"text":"that is very likely\nentirely new to science."},{"time":70961,"text":"A complete new species."},{"time":73117,"text":"Or how about this other transparent beauty"},{"time":75844,"text":"with a beating heart,"},{"time":77408,"text":"asexually growing on top of its head,"},{"time":80860,"text":"progeny that will move on\nto reproduce sexually."},{"time":84547,"text":"Let me say that again:"},{"time":86058,"text":"this animal is growing asexually\non top of its head,"},{"time":89768,"text":"progeny that is going to reproduce\nsexually in the next generation."},{"time":94960,"text":"A weird jellyfish?"},{"time":96796,"text":"Not quite."},{"time":98130,"text":"This is an ascidian."},{"time":99772,"text":"This is a group of animals"},{"time":101080,"text":"that now we know we share\nextensive genomic ancestry with,"},{"time":104851,"text":"and it is perhaps the closest\ninvertebrate species to our own."},{"time":110376,"text":"Meet your cousin,"},{"time":111769,"text":"Thalia democratica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113223,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115205,"text":"I'm pretty sure you didn't save a spot\nat your last family reunion"},{"time":119219,"text":"for Thalia,"},{"time":120675,"text":"but let me tell you,"},{"time":122351,"text":"these animals are profoundly related to us"},{"time":125703,"text":"in ways that we're just\nbeginning to understand."},{"time":130164,"text":"So, next time you hear anybody\nderisively telling you"},{"time":134313,"text":"that this type of research\nis a simple fishing expedition,"},{"time":138234,"text":"I hope that you'll remember\nthe trip that we just took."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141675,"text":"Today, many of the biological\nsciences only see value"},{"time":145539,"text":"in studying deeper what we already know --"},{"time":148112,"text":"in mapping already-discovered continents."},{"time":151099,"text":"But some of us are much more\ninterested in the unknown."},{"time":154849,"text":"We want to discover\ncompletely new continents,"},{"time":158817,"text":"and gaze at magnificent\nvistas of ignorance."},{"time":162674,"text":"We crave the experience\nof being completely baffled"},{"time":166794,"text":"by something we've never seen before."},{"time":168992,"text":"And yes, I agree"},{"time":170286,"text":"there's a lot of little ego satisfaction\nin being able to say,"},{"time":174110,"text":"\"Hey, I was the first one\nto discover that.\""},{"time":177102,"text":"But this is not\na self-aggrandizing enterprise,"},{"time":180031,"text":"because in this type\nof discovery research,"},{"time":182755,"text":"if you don't feel like a complete\nidiot most of the time,"},{"time":186397,"text":"you're just not sciencing hard enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188702,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":192014,"text":"So every summer I bring onto the deck\nof this little boat of ours"},{"time":198021,"text":"more and more things\nthat we know very little about."},{"time":202816,"text":"I would like tonight\nto tell you a story about life"},{"time":206328,"text":"that rarely gets told\nin an environment like this."},{"time":210915,"text":"From the vantage point of our 21st-century\nbiological laboratories,"},{"time":216274,"text":"we have begun to illuminate\nmany mysteries of life with knowledge."},{"time":220869,"text":"We sense that after centuries\nof scientific research,"},{"time":224530,"text":"we're beginning to make\nsignificant inroads"},{"time":226661,"text":"into understanding some of the most\nfundamental principles of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231223,"text":"Our collective optimism is reflected\nby the growth of biotechnology"},{"time":236248,"text":"across the globe,"},{"time":238326,"text":"striving to utilize scientific knowledge\nto cure human diseases."},{"time":243685,"text":"Things like cancer, aging,\ndegenerative diseases;"},{"time":248547,"text":"these are but some\nof the undesirables we wish to tame."},{"time":253817,"text":"I often wonder:"},{"time":255285,"text":"Why is it that we are having\nso much trouble"},{"time":258470,"text":"trying to solve the problem of cancer?"},{"time":261096,"text":"Is it that we're trying to solve\nthe problem of cancer,"},{"time":264374,"text":"and not trying to understand life?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267657,"text":"Life on this planet\nshares a common origin,"},{"time":270869,"text":"and I can summarize 3.5 billion years\nof the history of life on this planet"},{"time":275946,"text":"in a single slide."},{"time":277450,"text":"What you see here are representatives\nof all known species in our planet."},{"time":281321,"text":"In this immensity of life\nand biodiversity,"},{"time":284756,"text":"we occupy a rather unremarkable position."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287947,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":288987,"text":"Homo sapiens."},{"time":291016,"text":"The last of our kind."},{"time":293570,"text":"And though I don't really want\nto disparage at all"},{"time":296705,"text":"the accomplishments of our species,"},{"time":298700,"text":"as much as we wish it to be so\nand often pretend that it is,"},{"time":303710,"text":"we are not the measure of all things."},{"time":307311,"text":"We are, however, the measurers\nof many things."},{"time":311311,"text":"We relentlessly quantify,\nanalyze and compare,"},{"time":315081,"text":"and some of this is absolutely invaluable\nand indeed necessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319661,"text":"But this emphasis today on forcing\nbiological research to specialize"},{"time":326072,"text":"and to produce practical outcomes"},{"time":328644,"text":"is actually restricting our ability\nto interrogate life"},{"time":332222,"text":"to unacceptably narrow confines\nand unsatisfying depths."},{"time":337007,"text":"We are measuring an astonishingly\nnarrow sliver of life,"},{"time":342072,"text":"and hoping that those numbers\nwill save all of our lives."},{"time":346425,"text":"How narrow do you ask?"},{"time":347842,"text":"Well, let me give you a number."},{"time":349470,"text":"The National Oceanic and Atmospheric\nAdministration recently estimated"},{"time":354013,"text":"that about 95 percent of our oceans\nremain unexplored."},{"time":358674,"text":"Now let that sink in for a second."},{"time":361030,"text":"95 percent of our oceans\nremain unexplored."},{"time":365712,"text":"I think it's very safe to say"},{"time":367901,"text":"that we don't even know\nhow much about life we do not know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373810,"text":"So, it's not surprising\nthat every week in my field"},{"time":376759,"text":"we begin to see the addition\nof more and more new species"},{"time":379994,"text":"to this amazing tree of life."},{"time":382277,"text":"This one for example --"},{"time":383698,"text":"discovered earlier this summer,"},{"time":385628,"text":"new to science,"},{"time":386865,"text":"and now occupying its lonely branch\nin our family tree."},{"time":390973,"text":"What is even more tragic"},{"time":392148,"text":"is that we know about a bunch\nof other species of animals out there,"},{"time":395807,"text":"but their biology remains\nsorely under-studied."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399392,"text":"I'm sure some of you\nhave heard about the fact"},{"time":401750,"text":"that a starfish can actually\nregenerate its arm after it's lost."},{"time":405970,"text":"But some of you might not know"},{"time":407436,"text":"that the arm itself can actually\nregenerate a complete starfish."},{"time":412759,"text":"And there are animals out there\nthat do truly astounding things."},{"time":417461,"text":"I'm almost willing to bet"},{"time":419195,"text":"that many of you have never heard\nof the flatworm, Schmidtea mediterranea."},{"time":424423,"text":"This little guy right here"},{"time":426546,"text":"does things that essentially\njust blow my mind."},{"time":430131,"text":"You can grab one of these animals\nand cut it into 18 different fragments,"},{"time":434159,"text":"and each and every one of those fragments\nwill go on to regenerate"},{"time":437945,"text":"a complete animal"},{"time":439287,"text":"in under two weeks."},{"time":441694,"text":"18 heads, 18 bodies, 18 mysteries."},{"time":446348,"text":"For the past decade and a half or so,"},{"time":448768,"text":"I've been trying to figure out\nhow these little dudes do what they do,"},{"time":452502,"text":"and how they pull this magic trick off."},{"time":454725,"text":"But like all good magicians,"},{"time":456463,"text":"they're not really releasing\ntheir secrets readily to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459342,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":460572,"text":"So here we are,"},{"time":461754,"text":"after 20 years of essentially\nstudying these animals,"},{"time":466233,"text":"genome mapping, chin scratching,"},{"time":468564,"text":"and thousands of amputations\nand thousands of regenerations,"},{"time":471807,"text":"we still don't fully understand\nhow these animals do what they do."},{"time":476028,"text":"Each planarian an ocean unto itself,"},{"time":479648,"text":"full of unknowns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482476,"text":"One of the common characteristics"},{"time":484184,"text":"of all of these animals\nI've been talking to you about"},{"time":486820,"text":"is that they did not appear\nto have received the memo"},{"time":489607,"text":"that they need to behave\naccording to the rules"},{"time":492298,"text":"that we have derived from a handful\nof randomly selected animals"},{"time":496491,"text":"that currently populate the vast majority"},{"time":499237,"text":"of biomedical laboratories\nacross the world."},{"time":502117,"text":"Meet our Nobel Prize winners."},{"time":504371,"text":"Seven species, essentially,"},{"time":506397,"text":"that have produced for us the brunt\nof our understanding"},{"time":510023,"text":"of biological behavior today."},{"time":513172,"text":"This little guy right here --"},{"time":514988,"text":"three Nobel Prizes in 12 years."},{"time":518204,"text":"And yet, after all the attention\nthey have garnered,"},{"time":520984,"text":"and all the knowledge they have generated,"},{"time":523068,"text":"as well as the lion's share\nof the funding,"},{"time":525117,"text":"here we are standing [before] the same\nlitany of intractable problems"},{"time":529014,"text":"and many new challenges."},{"time":531220,"text":"And that's because, unfortunately,"},{"time":533059,"text":"these seven animals essentially correspond"},{"time":535697,"text":"to 0.0009 percent of all of the species\nthat inhabit the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543962,"text":"So I'm beginning to suspect"},{"time":546372,"text":"that our specialization is beginning\nto impede our progress at best,"},{"time":551157,"text":"and at worst, is leading us astray."},{"time":554235,"text":"That's because life\non this planet and its history"},{"time":557333,"text":"is the history of rule breakers."},{"time":559433,"text":"Life started on the face of this planet\nas single-cell organisms,"},{"time":562804,"text":"swimming for millions\nof years in the ocean,"},{"time":565150,"text":"until one of those creatures decided,"},{"time":567460,"text":"\"I'm going to do things differently today;"},{"time":569543,"text":"today I would like to invent\nsomething called multicellularity,"},{"time":572575,"text":"and I'm going to do this.\""},{"time":573872,"text":"And I'm sure it wasn't a popular\ndecision at the time --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":576548,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577599,"text":"but somehow, it managed to do it."},{"time":579229,"text":"And then, multicellular\norganisms began to populate"},{"time":581819,"text":"all these ancestral oceans,"},{"time":583219,"text":"and they thrived."},{"time":584431,"text":"And we have them here today."},{"time":586789,"text":"Land masses began to emerge\nfrom the surface of the oceans,"},{"time":589810,"text":"and another creature thought,"},{"time":591288,"text":"\"Hey, that looks like a really nice\npiece of real estate."},{"time":594101,"text":"I'd like to move there.\""},{"time":595376,"text":"\"Are you crazy?"},{"time":596559,"text":"You're going to desiccate out there.\nNothing can live out of water.\""},{"time":599867,"text":"But life found a way,"},{"time":601048,"text":"and there are organisms\nnow that live on land."},{"time":603395,"text":"Once on land, they may have\nlooked up into the sky"},{"time":605817,"text":"and said, \"It would be nice\nto go to the clouds,"},{"time":608100,"text":"I'm going to fly.\""},{"time":609275,"text":"\"You can't break the law of gravity,\nthere's no way you can fly.\""},{"time":612374,"text":"And yet, nature has invented --"},{"time":614683,"text":"multiple and independent times --"},{"time":616714,"text":"ways to fly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618368,"text":"I love to study these animals\nthat break the rules,"},{"time":620909,"text":"because every time they break a rule,\nthey invent something new"},{"time":624562,"text":"that made it possible for us\nto be able to be here today."},{"time":628624,"text":"These animals did not get the memo."},{"time":630918,"text":"They break the rules."},{"time":632642,"text":"So if we're going to study animals\nthat break the rules,"},{"time":635461,"text":"shouldn't how we study them\nalso break the rules?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":639666,"text":"I think we need to renew\nour spirit of exploration."},{"time":643440,"text":"Rather than bring nature\ninto our laboratories"},{"time":645948,"text":"and interrogate it there,"},{"time":647287,"text":"we need to bring our science"},{"time":649017,"text":"into the majestic laboratory\nthat is nature,"},{"time":651946,"text":"and there, with our modern\ntechnological armamentarium,"},{"time":655881,"text":"interrogate every new form\nof life we find,"},{"time":658731,"text":"and any new biological attribute\nthat we may find."},{"time":662486,"text":"We actually need to bring\nall of our intelligence"},{"time":666664,"text":"to becoming stupid again --"},{"time":668780,"text":"clueless [before] the immensity\nof the unknown."},{"time":673116,"text":"Because after all,"},{"time":674501,"text":"science is not really about knowledge."},{"time":676684,"text":"Science is about ignorance."},{"time":679449,"text":"That's what we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680838,"text":"Once, Antoine de Saint-Exup√©ry wrote,"},{"time":683993,"text":"\"If you want to build a ship,"},{"time":685818,"text":"don't drum up people to collect wood"},{"time":687786,"text":"and don't assign them tasks and work,"},{"time":690112,"text":"but rather teach them to long\nfor the endless immensity of the sea ...\""},{"time":694646,"text":"As a scientist and a teacher,"},{"time":696374,"text":"I like to paraphrase this to read"},{"time":698359,"text":"that we scientists need\nto teach our students"},{"time":701541,"text":"to long for the endless\nimmensity of the sea"},{"time":704016,"text":"that is our ignorance."},{"time":706768,"text":"We Homo sapiens are the only\nspecies we know of"},{"time":710657,"text":"that is driven to scientific inquiry."},{"time":713645,"text":"We, like all other species on this planet,"},{"time":715803,"text":"are inextricably woven\ninto the history of life on this planet."},{"time":720989,"text":"And I think I'm a little wrong\nwhen I say that life is a mystery,"},{"time":724180,"text":"because I think that life\nis actually an open secret"},{"time":726915,"text":"that has been beckoning our species\nfor millennia to understand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731344,"text":"So I ask you:"},{"time":732969,"text":"Aren't we the best chance\nthat life has to know itself?"},{"time":737053,"text":"And if so,"},{"time":738228,"text":"what the heck are we waiting for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":740368,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741593,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}